[[File:Flag of Malaysia.svg|210px|right|The [[Flag of Malaysia]]]] [[Image:Malaysia (orthographic projection).svg|right|188px]] [[Image:Malaysia-CIA WFB Map.png|thumb|An enlargeable map of [[Malaysia]]]] {{See also|Index of Malaysia-related articles}}
'''[[Malaysia]]''' is a [[List of sovereign states|sovereign country]] located on the [[Malay Peninsula]] and a northern portion of the [[Island of Borneo]] in [[Southeast Asia]].<ref name=CIA_World_Factbook>{{cite web|date=July 2, 2009|url=https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/geos/my.html|title=Malaysia|work=[[The World Factbook]]|publisher=[[United States]] [[Central Intelligence Agency]]|accessdate=July 23, 2009}}</ref> Malaysia comprises [[States of Malaysia|thirteen states and three federal territories]] with a total land area of {{convert|329847|km2|sqmi|}}.<ref>Article 1. Constitution of Malaysia.</ref> The [[Capital (political)|capital]] of Malaysia is [[Kuala Lumpur]], while [[Putrajaya]] is the seat of the federal government.
The population stands at over 25 million.<ref name=CIA_World_Factbook/> The country is separated into two regionsâ[[Peninsular Malaysia]] and [[East Malaysia|Malaysian Borneo]]âby the [[South China Sea]].<ref name=CIA_World_Factbook/> Malaysia borders [[Thailand]], [[Indonesia]], [[Singapore]], [[Brunei]], the [[Philippines]],<ref name=CIA_World_Factbook/> and Vietnam. The country is located near the equator and experiences a [[tropics|tropical]] climate.<ref name=CIA_World_Factbook/>
Malaysia is headed by the [[Yang di-Pertuan Agong]] and politically led by a [[Prime Minister of Malaysia|Prime Minister]].<ref>Article 33. Constitution of Malaysia.</ref><ref>Article 43. Constitution of Malaysia.</ref> The government is closely modeled after the [[Westminster]] [[parliamentary system]].<ref>The [[Federation of International Trade Associations]]. [http://www.fita.org/countries/malaysia.html?ma_rubrique=cadre General Information of Malaysia]. Retrieved December 7, 2007.</ref><!---- need better sources... --->
