== Notes == <div class="references-small"> # {{note|UMNO}} UMNO was deregistered in 1988 and the Prime Minister of Malaysia formed a new party known as United Malays National Organisation (Baru) on February 16, 1988. The term "Baru" or "New" was removed by a constitutional amendment on July of the same year. # {{note|PBS}} The United Sabah Party (Parti Bersatu Sabah) was a member of Barisan Nasional from its establishment in 1985 until its withdrawal from the coalition in 1990. The party rejoined the coalition in 2002.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.malaysiatoday.com/Politic/parti-bersatu-sabah-pbs.html |title=Parti Bersatu Sabah (PBS) |accessdate=2008-06-24 |work=MalaysiaToday.com |date=2008-06-05 }} {{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}}</ref> # {{note|PAS}} The Pan-Malaysian Islamic Party entered a coalition with the former Alliance Party in 1972 and subsequently joined the Barisan Nasional coalition when it was founded in 1974. It withdrew from the coalition in 1977.<ref>{{cite book |title=Islam in South-East Asia |last=Hooker |first=M. B. |authorlink= |coauthors= |year=1983 |publisher=Brill Archive |location=Boston |isbn=9004068449 |pages=203â204 }}</ref> </div>
